name: Rafale
description: The Dassault Rafale (French pronunciation: ​[ʁafal], literally meaning "gust of wind",[9] and "burst of fire" in a more military sense)[10] is a French twin-engine, canard delta wing, multirole fighter aircraft designed and built by Dassault Aviation.

name: Saab JAS 39 Gripen
description: The Saab JAS 39 Gripen (IPA: [²griːp.ɛn]; English: "griffin")[Nb 3][7] is a light single-engine multirole fighter aircraft manufactured by the Swedish aerospace company Saab.

name: Sukhoi Su-24
description: The Sukhoi Su-24 (NATO reporting name: Fencer) is a supersonic, all-weather attack aircraft developed in the Soviet Union.

name: Su-35
description: The Sukhoi Su-35 (Russian: Сухой Су-35; NATO reporting name: Flanker-E) is the designation for two improved derivatives of the Su-27 air-defence fighter.
